&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Haematology/Oncology Daycare&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are exciting times for the progressive, rapidly expanding Haematology &amp; Chemotherapy Daycare Unit at UCH. We provide highly specialised care for a wide variety of patient groups within haematology and oncology, between 8am and 8pm Monday to Sunday. Staff in this friendly and supportive team develop a range of advanced skills and knowledge by rotating between the 4 main areas of Daycare. Our Red Cell/General Haematology/Oncology area provides holistic care for haemoglobinopathy patients as well as follow-up and treatments for patients who have undergone high dose chemotherapy and bone marrow transplant. We have a busy and varied Oncology and Haematology chemotherapy suite; and a highly respected Apheresis service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Nursing Assistant Haematology &amp; Chemotherapy Daycare&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full-time Band 4 vacancy within the exciting, and innovative Daycare Team. The successful candidate will be part of a large dynamic team caring for patients with both Haematological and Oncological malignancies. The candidate must have an NVQ level 2/3 qualification (or equivalent) and have completed an Advanced skills course. They must also demonstrate good communication skills including an ability to utilise IT applications to ensure the success of this role. Venepuncture is desirable although not essential as training will be provided to the successful candidate. The candidate will be responsible for co-managing a small team of nursing assistants so should show evidence of leadership skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Keane helen.keane@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
